<p>The basic structure to implement schedule project. You have 3 objects to implement yours views, because the logic is implemented in this gem.</p>

<h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>

<p>Add this line to your applicationâ€™s Gemfile:
	{% highlight ruby %}
    gem â€˜agendare-scheduleâ€™
    {% endhighlight %}</p>

<p>And then execute:
	{% highlight ruby %}
    $ bundle
    {% endhighlight %}</p>

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>

<p>Create controlllers.
{% highlight ruby %}
     rails  generate agendare:install controllers
{% endhighlight %}</p>

<p>Create models.
{% highlight ruby %}
     rails  generate agendare:install models
{% endhighlight %}</p>

<p>Create migrations.
{% highlight ruby %}
     rails  generate agendare:install migrations
{% endhighlight %}</p>

<p>Import the structure to database.
{% highlight ruby %}
     rake db:migrate
{% endhighlight %}</p>

<p>Add this lines in your config/routes.rb
{% highlight ruby %}
	 resources :schedules
	 resources :scheduleds
	 resources :users 
{% endhighlight %}</p>

